                'title'            => 'Speed Bingo: Rules and Tips for Fast-Paced Play',
                'slug'             => 'speed-bingo-rules-and-tips',
                'category'         => 'guide',
                'reading_time'     => '4 min read',
                'meta_description' => 'Speed bingo is a fast, exciting variant using 30 balls and a 3x3 card. Learn the rules, how to set it up, and tips for running a thrilling speed bingo session.',
                'excerpt'          => 'Speed bingo uses a 3×3 card and only 30 balls — games last under 3 minutes. Here\'s how to play and why it\'s perfect for quick entertainment.',
                'body'             => '<p>Speed bingo (also called 30-ball bingo) is the fastest bingo format in existence. Games can be over in under two minutes, which makes it perfect as a quick filler game, a warm-up activity, or a high-energy round between slower standard games.</p>
<h2>Speed Bingo Rules</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Card:</strong> 3×3 grid with 9 numbers (no free space)</li><li><strong>Ball pool:</strong> 1–30 only</li><li><strong>Winning condition:</strong> Full house — all 9 numbers marked</li><li><strong>Average game length:</strong> 90 seconds to 3 minutes</li></ul>
<h2>Why Players Love Speed Bingo</h2>
<ul><li>Constant action — no waiting around</li><li>High frequency of wins per hour</li><li>Great for short attention spans (younger players, parties)</li><li>Ideal for digital play on mobile devices</li></ul>
<h2>Running Speed Bingo with Funny Bingo</h2>
<p>Standard <a href="/">Funny Bingo</a> uses 75 balls, but you can simulate speed bingo by setting auto-call to 3 seconds and stopping the game once a winner is confirmed. The rapid pace creates electric energy in the room.</p>
<h2>Speed Bingo at Events</h2>
<ul><li>Use it as a warm-up before standard bingo rounds</li><li>Run 10–15 speed rounds as a standalone activity at parties</li><li>Award a prize for every round — with games lasting 2 minutes, this is affordable and exciting</li><li>Use it as a tiebreaker between players who tied in standard bingo</li></ul>
<h2>Tips for Callers</h2>
<ul><li>Call numbers rapidly but clearly</li><li>Don\'t pause between calls — speed is the whole point</li><li>Have the next number ready the moment the previous one is marked</li></ul>',
