                'title'            => 'Bingo Accessories: The Complete Buyer\'s Guide',
                'slug'             => 'bingo-accessories-buyers-guide',
                'category'         => 'guide',
                'reading_time'     => '5 min read',
                'meta_description' => 'From daubers to ball cages, discover the best bingo accessories for home games, fundraisers, and bingo halls. A complete guide to bingo equipment.',
                'excerpt'          => 'The right bingo accessories elevate your game night from casual to professional. Here\'s everything you need and what to look for when buying.',
                'body'             => '<p>Whether you\'re setting up a home game night, running a church fundraiser, or equipping a community bingo hall, the right accessories make a significant difference in the experience. Here\'s a complete guide to bingo equipment.</p>
<h2>Bingo Ball Sets</h2>
<p>Traditional bingo uses 75 numbered balls (1–75) in a wire cage or electronic blower. For home use:</p>
<ul><li><strong>Cage and balls set:</strong> Classic hand-cranked wire cage with wooden or plastic balls. Affordable and reliable for home use.</li><li><strong>Electronic blower:</strong> Air-powered ball display. More professional feel, used in bingo halls. Higher cost.</li><li><strong>Digital caller (recommended):</strong> <a href="/">Funny Bingo</a> replaces all physical equipment with a free browser app that calls numbers by voice and tracks everything automatically.</li></ul>
<h2>Bingo Cards</h2>
<ul><li><strong>Paper cards:</strong> Disposable, cheap to print, easy to distribute</li><li><strong>Laminated cards:</strong> Reusable, more expensive upfront but cost-effective long-term</li><li><strong>Digital cards:</strong> Free via Funny Bingo QR code — no printing or laminating required</li></ul>
<h2>Daubers (Bingo Markers)</h2>
<p>Daubers are ink-filled markers used to blot called numbers on paper cards. What to look for:</p>
<ul><li><strong>Ink visibility:</strong> Should be bright and opaque — avoid daubers with thin ink</li><li><strong>Tip size:</strong> Standard tip (3/4") works for most cards; large tip for seniors or accessibility needs</li><li><strong>Colors:</strong> Buy assorted colors so players can differentiate their cards</li><li><strong>Ink type:</strong> Water-based is safer; permanent ink for laminated cards</li></ul>
<h2>Bingo Chips and Tokens</h2>
<p>For reusable physical cards, chips or tokens replace daubers. Poker chips, dried beans, or dedicated bingo chips all work. Advantage: cards can be reused round after round without reprinting.</p>
<h2>Master Board Display</h2>
<p>Traditional halls use a physical master board with numbered slots. Modern solution: Funny Bingo\'s on-screen master board displays all 75 balls in a 5×15 grid — called balls are highlighted automatically, saving significant cost and setup time.</p>
<h2>Portable PA System</h2>
<p>For events with 30+ players, a PA speaker ensures everyone can hear the caller clearly. A Bluetooth speaker with microphone input is the most convenient option for mobile events.</p>',
